[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-27T17:37:11+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Grayscale Arc logo on pink and blue background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/whZJ4izWTIKVp_VXfhJ0rEiXc8I=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73616361/STK283_ARC_BROWSER_B.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ZrPN4n\">Arc creator The Browser Company has officially <a href=\"https://arc.net/blog/investing-in-security\">started a bug bounty program</a> to keep its growing Chromium-based browser\u2019s security in check. The company is also launching a new security bulletin to maintain \u201ctransparent and proactive communication\u201d with users and researchers on bug fixes and reports.</p>\n<p id=\"PIfrxr\">These security revisions followed <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/20/24249919/arc-browser-boost-firebase-vulnerability-patched\">a devastating bug</a> a researcher found and reported to the company that would\u2019ve allowed bad actors to insert arbitrary code", "id": 1227477, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/27/24256271/arc-browser-bug-bounty-security-bulletin", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Arc browser adds security bulletins and bug bounties", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-27T16:51:38+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Graphic photo illustration of Donald Trump.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/8qPCr16Hr234x-JnxRpKEAne0To=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73616233/STK466_ELECTION_2024_CVirginia_E.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Cath Virginia / The Verge | Photos from Scott Olson, Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"KkTLls\">The US Department of Justice <a href=\"https://www.justice.gov/opa/pr/three-irgc-cyber-actors-indicted-hack-and-leak-operation-designed-influence-2024-us\">has charged three Iranian nationals</a> linked with a cyberattack against Donald Trump\u2019s presidential campaign, according to <a href=\"https://www.justice.gov/opa/media/1371191/dl\">an indictment</a> on Friday.</p>\n<p id=\"hqB43w\">The three hackers, all of whom have ties to Iran\u2019s Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps, allegedly gained access to the accounts of campaign officials using social engineering and spearphishing, a tactic that attempts to trick", "id": 1227164, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/27/24256133/doj-iranian-hackers-donald-trump-campaign", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "DOJ indicts Iranians for alleged Trump campaign \u2018hack-and-leak\u2019 scheme", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-27T16:04:06+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/SocvhiKsSuYjqNGtIyZd-nPK1nQ=/68x0:644x384/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73616132/pepe_tow_fire_batteries.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>A container truck burns outside the Port of Los Angeles.</em> | Image: <a class=\"ql-link\" href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/DAZ08n9PfVT/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\">Pepe\u2019s Towing</a></figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"WZfpaD\">A truck full of lithium-ion batteries is burning in Los Angeles, shutting down ports and a bridge. It\u2019s not clear what the batteries were for \u2014 but LA\u2019s Vincent Thomas Bridge, leading to the Port of Los Angeles and the nearby Port of Long Beach, has been shut down for at least 15 hours now while local firefighters let the truck burn. State Route 47 was also closed in both directions as of a couple of hours ago.</p>\n<p id=\"M6K5uF\">Amazingly, a local towing company caught the explosion on camera from a nearby drone:</p>\n<div id=\"3TEn2X\">\n<", "id": 1227165, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/27/24256161/los-angeles-overturned-truck-battery-fire-lithium-ion-port-bridge-closed", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "A truck full of batteries has been burning for almost a full day, shutting down ports in LA", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-27T15:36:43+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of the Threads app logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Oj04dYyaoVARt5Vmdz7Klp2EqVg=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73616069/STK156_Instagram_threads_2.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"3IYYJP\">Meta is rolling out the ability to tag your location on your Threads posts. If you have the feature, you\u2019ll see a pin in the post composer that you can tap so you can include where you are.</p>\n<p id=\"2AS5Xy\">Note that adding your location to a Threads post doesn\u2019t share an exact pin on a map. Instead, the feature lets you give your users an approximate idea of your location by sharing things like a city name, a neighborhood, or a restaurant. And if you see a Threads post that includes a location, you can tap that location to see other posts from the same place. </p>\n<p id=\"QeymJB\">I have the feature, and I\u2019ve been messing around with it. When I tap the", "id": 1226801, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/27/24256160/meta-threads-tag-location-instagram", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Threads now lets you tag your location", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-27T14:41:58+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A robotic arm with its articulated hand detached and crawling on its own.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Sl6axlJJ5CLOtS5USm9T61NEnVw=/0x0:1556x1037/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73615955/robotarm.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>This robotic arm\u2019s articulated hand can detach and crawl around on its own.</em> | Screenshot: YouTube</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"WrCTZB\">Researchers from the \u00c9cole polytechnique f\u00e9d\u00e9rale de Lausanne (EPFL) in Switzerland have developed an articulated hand that can extend the reach of a robotic arm by detaching and crawling away on its own to grab things. The research was recently presented at the <a href=\"https://icra40.ieee.org/\">International Conference on Robotics and Automation</a> (ICRA) and was <a href=\"https://spectrum.ieee.org/epfl-lasa\">spotted by <em>IEEE Spectrum</em> magazine</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"DTIPn9\">Due to their strength and speed, robotic arms are typically permanently attac", "id": 1226802, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/27/24256001/robot-arm-hand-crawl-grasp-epfl", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "This robot arm can detach its hand to grab things", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-27T14:35:18+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"fiery satellite going like a comet towards earth\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/9Ftxfla2vsEf2SYe-NVJUxyE9Fs=/24x0:936x608/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73615934/ESA_Space_Debris_project___DRACO_article.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>An illustration of DRACO getting destroyed in Earth\u2019s atmosphere. | Image: ESA</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"AybTUL\">The European Space Agency (ESA) plans to launch a satellite into Earth\u2019s orbit in 2027 to <a href=\"https://www.esa.int/Space_Safety/Draco_mission_made_for_destruction\">watch it get wrecked as it re-enters the atmosphere</a>. The project is intended to help understand how exactly satellites break apart so that they can learn how to prevent the creation of more space debris.</p>\n<p id=\"RiQyEy\">Space junk <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/12/24218442/space-junk-debris-satellite-news-storystream\">is becoming a bigger problem</a> as we send more satellites into orbit, but ", "id": 1226460, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/27/24255990/esa-draco-mission-satellite-space-junk-zero-debris", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Europe\u2019s space agency will destroy a brand-new satellite in 2027 just to see what happens", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-27T14:30:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of the Nintendo Museum in Kyoto.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/5Mq-_T0GdT8qNQbj9ClSWpSj6lo=/0x0:1920x1280/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73615918/Exterior_Photo_spot.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Nintendo</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>The Nintendo Museum in Kyoto is a slick and playful trek through the company\u2019s century-long history. But it\u2019s lacking much in the way of revelations.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/27/24256070/nintendo-museum-kyoto-tour-shigeru-miyamoto\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1226461, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/27/24256070/nintendo-museum-kyoto-tour-shigeru-miyamoto", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Nintendo\u2019s shiny new museum needs more dirt", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-27T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of Windows Recall\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/dMhpZ_8ufYqwDkmAW0QW7moD5TE=/0x0:1320x880/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73615662/windowsrecall.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Microsoft</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"uYC6Xq\">In response to security concerns, Microsoft is detailing how it has overhauled its controversial AI-powered Recall feature that creates screenshots of mostly everything you see or do on a computer. Recall was originally supposed to debut with <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/20/24160486/microsoft-copilot-plus-ai-arm-chips-pc-surface-event\">Copilot Plus PCs</a> in June, but Microsoft has spent the past few months reworking the security behind it to make it an opt-in experience that you can now fully remove from Windows if you want.</p>\n<p id=\"K4P5J2\">\u201cI\u2019m actually really excited about how nerdy we got on the security architecture,\u201d says David Weston, vice president of ente", "id": 1226106, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/27/24255721/microsoft-windows-recall-ai-security-improvements-overhaul-uninstall", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Microsoft\u2019s more secure Windows Recall feature can also be uninstalled by users", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-27T11:37:57+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"The CNN logo in white against a red background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/9VzIzlBo_GF9JLqDVUwYrGehYM4=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73615426/CNN_logo.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>CNN chairman Mark Thompson announced plans to introduce a digital subscription business in July.</em> | Image: CNN</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"k8DyQT\">CNN<em> </em>will put some of its digital content behind a subscription paywall starting next month,  <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2024/09/26/business/media/cnn-paywall.html\"><em>The New York Times</em> reports</a>. The experiment will test similar subscription models to those used by publications like <em>The New Yorker</em>, <em>Wired</em>, and <em>The Wall Street Journal, </em>with CNN<em> </em>reportedly hoping to bring in additional revenue amid a decline in cable TV viewership.</p>\n<p id=\"5euMYK\">A \u201cmetered\u201d paywall feature is set to launch sometime in early", "id": 1225608, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/27/24255900/cnn-paywall-digital-subscription-mark-thompson", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "CNN will start locking some articles behind a paywall", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-27T11:29:47+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Amtrak train on track with a body of water in the background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/7GYfva8VptChOsV8peVRq3Cvm4w=/62x0:2498x1624/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73615389/2014_0624_ACS64_BushRiverBridgeIMG_2657_scaled.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Trains are cool but aren\u2019t always cheaper to ride.</em> | Image: Amtrak</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ei7O2D\">Amtrak fares and trip suggestions <a href=\"https://media.amtrak.com/2024/09/amtrak-debuts-new-integration-with-google-to-support-more-sustainable-transportation-choices/\">are getting integrated into Google Search</a> as part of Google\u2019s efforts to offer greener ways of travel over flights. Now, when you search for airline fares on Google or Google Flights between destinations with Amtrak terminals, you\u2019ll also get suggestions for train rides that you can click through to Amtrak\u2019s site for purchase.</p>\n<p id=\"B3cKiR\">Google <a href=\"https://blog.google/outre", "id": 1225609, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/27/24255817/google-search-flights-amtrak-train-suggestions-tickets", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Now searches on Google Flights will suggest Amtrak train rides, too", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-27T11:22:42+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo collage of various MagSafe chargers.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/2w7Phksq07lEVBqIRIJ_oasnPkg=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/71769681/247290_Buying_Guide_MagSafe_Charger_CVirginia.6.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Thanks to Qi2, there are way more great chargers for your MagSafe phone than ever before.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23505846/best-magsafe-magnetic-chargers-apple-iphone\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1225086, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23505846/best-magsafe-magnetic-chargers-apple-iphone", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The best MagSafe and Qi2 chargers for your iPhone", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-27T10:51:30+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Steam logo on a pink background, surrounded by Valve logos.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/bZhbBwX-hMHWL-eOW65SnPtnaTo=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73615255/STK139_Stream_Kradtke_01.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"urNIkS\">Steam just removed its forced arbitration policy, opening the door for lawsuits against its parent company, Valve. In <a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/games/593110/announcements/detail/4696781406111167992?utm_source=SteamDB\">an update on Thursday</a>, Steam says <a href=\"https://store.steampowered.com/subscriber_agreement?snr=2_groupannouncements_detail_#10\">its subscriber agreement</a> \u201cnow provides that any disputes are to go forward in court instead of arbitration.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"Mo4CY6\">Many companies include a forced arbitration clause in their user agreement, waiving a person\u2019s right to a trial in court. Arbitration involves sett", "id": 1225087, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/27/24255841/steam-forced-arbitration-policy-lawsuit", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Steam will let you sue Valve now", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-27T09:03:09+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of Meta Connect, over a Vergecast illustration.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0bh9wfkkzJA0ACufKzimVNO17lE=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73615011/VST_0928_Site.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Alex Parkin / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"uO1Oo3\">You can\u2019t buy Meta\u2019s most impressive new product, the smart glasses codenamed Orion. You might be able to buy something sort of like them, a few years from now, but most of us will never get to so much as wear them. That doesn\u2019t necessarily make them less impressive, though, or less important. Orion is a statement of purpose from Meta: that AR glasses really are the future, and that we\u2019re eventually going to get there.</p>\n<p id=\"wq2J8x\">On <a href=\"https://link.chtbl.com/vergecast\">this episode of <em>The Vergecast</em></a>, <em>The Verge</em>\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/authors/alex-heath\">Alex Heath</a> joins the show to tell us ", "id": 1224191, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/27/24255557/meta-orion-quest-smart-glasses-ar-connect-vergecast", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Meta\u2019s new smart glasses look like the future", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-09-27T08:13:54+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A picture taken during LG\u2019s webOS Summit of Razer\u2019s new ULL-supported Bluetooth controller\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Tum3VklfCRUjE8wliCytmTXzlyg=/33x0:1887x1236/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73614885/Razer_LG_BT_ULL_controller.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The new ULL-supported controller (seen right) was tested against an unspecified standard Bluetooth gamepad (left).</em> | Image: LG</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"3Lvth0\">LG has teamed up with Razer and MediaTek to develop <a href=\"https://www.lgnewsroom.com/2024/09/lg-teams-up-with-razer-and-mediatek-to-present-first-ever-bluetooth-ultra-low-latency-technology/\">a new Bluetooth gaming controller</a> that could greatly reduce the input lag for cloud-based gaming. According to LG, it\u2019s the first controller to utilize Ultra-Low Latency (ULL) Bluetooth technology \u2014 an <a href=\"https://www.bluetooth.com/specificatio